word_group.brief_definition: 精心描述的乡村；用心描述的乡村

bilingual.source: Nowadays, millions of Chinese leave the countryside to search for work in the cities.
bilingual.target: 如今，数百万中国人离开农村去城市找工作。

bilingual.source: In the countryside, many families make a living by herding sheep.
bilingual.target: 在农村，很多家庭都靠放羊为生。

bilingual.source: The living conditions in the city are much better than in the countryside.
bilingual.target: 城市的生活条件比农村好很多。

bilingual.source: The school organized students to experience cultivating land in the countryside.
bilingual.target: 学校组织学生去农村体验种田的生活。

bilingual.source: The implementation of agriculture, countryside, and farmers policies is crucial for rural development.
bilingual.target: 三农政策的实施对农村发展至关重要。

bilingual.source: In the countryside, many people choose to be engaged in agriculture rather than work in the city.
bilingual.target: 在农村，很多人选择务农而不是去城市工作。

bilingual.source: We must pay attention to agriculture, countryside, and farmers issues to promote sustainable rural economic development.
bilingual.target: 我们必须重视三农问题，促进农村经济的可持续发展。

bilingual.source: More people like to work in the countryside nowadays.
bilingual.target: 现在越来越多的人喜欢在农村工作。

bilingual.source: So he made up his mind to build his own home in the countryside.
bilingual.target: 所以他下定决心要在农村建自己的家。

bilingual.source: As a junior boy from the countryside, I could hardly keep up.
bilingual.target: 作为一个来自农村的初中生，我几乎跟不上。

list.abstract: countryside（[ˈkʌntrisaɪd]），英语单词，作名词用，为农村；农村地区；乡间。短语搭配有in the countryside（在乡村；在乡下；在农村），例句为“I feel much freer in the countryside.（我在乡下感觉自由多了）”。 countryside名词类近义词有ruralarea、campagna，名词为country，复数为countrysides。

yingyinNormal.en: By 2030, 350 million people, the population of the United States, are expected to move from the countryside to the cities.
yingyinNormal.zh: 到2030年，预计有三亿五千万人，相当于美国的人口总量，将会从农村迁移到城市。

yingyinNormal.en: Today, Peppa and her family are driving out to the countryside.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今天佩奇和家人一起开车到郊外。

yingyinNormal.en: I love camping. Since we are in the countryside, I thought we can spend the day looking at nature.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我喜欢露营。既然我们来到了郊外，我觉得我们可以去看看大自然的风景。

yingyinNormal.en: Daddy, what will we see in the countryside? We'll see birds and trees and flowers and bees. Dine-saw.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们会在郊外看见什么呢？会看见鸟，树木，花朵和蜜蜂。恐龙！

yingyinNormal.en: I told him of a holiday my family had taken once out on the seaside at Pendeen in Cornwall. My brother and I roamed the countryside.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我跟他说过我们全家人的一次度假经历，到康沃尔郡彭丁的海边，我和我哥哥在乡间漫步。

yingyinNormal.en: But it'll be in an odd phrase in an on-line blog, or an unexpected trip to the countryside, or a misplaced lonely hearts ad. Your move!
yingyinNormal.zh: 答案也许是网上博客一处奇怪用词，一次临时乡间旅行，或者发错地方的征友广告。该你走了!
